categories.summary: The seller mentions that the rate offered by Vila Galé is cheaper than what they found on Booking.com and includes breakfast.

The seller inquires about airport transfer services offered by the hotel. The seller also mentions a hot tub jacuzzi, but the buyer clarifies that the hotel only has a sauna and massages, not a jacuzzi.
The seller is trying to book a room and asks if the hotel can offer a better rate than what she found on a booking website.

summary.text: This is a hotel room booking call between Sofia Martinez (the buyer) and a Vila Galé hotel reservation agent (the seller). Sofia wanted to book a family room for one night (August 2nd to 3rd) in Cascais for two adults and two children, seeking a better rate than she found online. The agent offered a junior suite for 286 euros, including breakfast, which Sofia accepted after confirming breakfast hours. Sofia inquired about airport transfer services but was informed the hotel doesn't offer them directly, but reception could provide taxi contacts. She confirmed her details, including email and phone number, while explaining her family was temporarily moving out of their house. The agent clarified the hotel's wellness center includes a sauna and massages, but no jacuzzi. The agent finalized the booking with payment upon arrival and provided the reservation number (8476952). The agent emailed confirmation, and the call concluded.

items.original_text: Speak with reception at Vila Galé hotel in Cascais directly to see if they have a contact for a taxi to arrange a transfer to the airport.
